   {:e #blake3 "fcc1177e6d7f2d3b4fb7cc4e46f5e473b059c2ee14f4783f6132506eb811e7ee" :a :harvest/accomplishments :v "Session entity: :recon/trace-a727f3ddd6603149; Session entity: :recon/trace-192dc3b0726bfa11; Session entity: :recon/trace-b7e8483f83832846; Session entity: :recon/trace-b274d3aa31d032d0; Session entity: :recon/trace-e48cb4beed4150ba; Session entity: :recon/trace-ca66e680be87f5d3; Session entity: :recon/trace-cfe771c277d103e5; Session entity: :recon/trace-c0937a60b0bc89fd; Session entity: :task/t-7c926e62; Session entity: unnamed entity; Session entity: :recon/trace-7349a8cacd5bae20; Session entity: :recon/trace-8ee2ec00e2c9f9d5; Session entity: :task/t-dad6123f; Session entity: :recon/trace-5556218e9ba7f585\nSession entity: :task/t-583e0ce0; DOGFOOD-2 Session 3 RETRY RESULT: Composite 3.48/10 on fresh Go CLI store. CONCEPT COLLAPSE: All 10 observations assigned to ALL 4 main concepts (jaccard=1.00). The hash embedder (HashEmbedder, 256-dim token hashing) produces embeddings where cosine similarity between any observation and any innate concept is 0.34-0.74 — all above the JOIN_THRESHOLD of 0.20. Every observation trivially matches every concept. Multi-membership becomes concept collapse: 100% multi-rate but 0% discriminative value. Entropy H=1.57 PASSES the threshold but is meaningless when it measures uniform assignment, not genuine distribution. Frontier steering degenerated to 2 templates repeated 10 times. Holistic score 3.65/10 — below Session 043's 6.7/10 (which used a pre-populated store with some concept differentiation from prior sessions). ROOT CAUSE ANALYSIS: The hash embedder maps text to 256 binary dimensions via token hashing. Innate concept descriptions ('Parts of the system and their boundaries — packages, modules, crates, files, services') share vocabulary overlap with ANY software observation. Cosine similarity > 0.20 is trivially achievable. The JOIN_THRESHOLD of 0.20 is far too low for hash embeddings. REMEDIATION PATH: (1) IMMEDIATE: Raise JOIN_THRESHOLD to 0.50+ for hash embedder. (2) STRUCTURAL: Use model2vec embeddings which produce semantic similarity, not keyword overlap. (3) FUNDAMENTAL: The innate concept descriptions are too broad — 'invariants' matches anything about rules, constraints, assertions, which is everything in a spec-management codebase. Traces to: INV-EMBEDDING-004, ADR-FOUNDATION-030, INV-GUIDANCE-014.; Session entity: :task/t-8a01aa8f; DOGFOOD-2 Session 3 retry methodology: The Go CLI store (290 txns, pre-CCE schema) is a confounding variable. First-principles reasoning demands a fresh braid init for a controlled initial condition: (1) C7 self-bootstrap — braid's first act should be verifying its own coherence from cold start. (2) Scientific method — the experiment must be reproducible; a 290-txn legacy store is uncontrolled. (3) Feature testing — Session 044/045 features (multi-membership, frontier steering, E[delta-F(S)] scoring, concept-level OAR, entity_label improvements) are all first-observation-onwards features, so a fresh store is the cleanest test. (4) The Session 037 pattern (3 parallel subagents on fresh init) was the most rigorous prior methodology, but since we're testing ONE feature (CCE quality) from three measurement angles, a single agent doing the full lifecycle produces all three measurements without fragmenting the concept model. Protocol: rm Go CLI .braid/ -> fresh braid init -> one subagent runs 10 diverse observations -> harvest -> measure concept entropy + steering actionability + prediction error -> score. Traces to: INV-GUIDANCE-014, ADR-FOUNDATION-030, C7.; DOGFOOD measurement protocol: Three metrics with explicit falsification conditions. METRIC 1 (Concept Distribution Entropy): Query concept names and member counts after harvest. Compute Shannon entropy H = -sum(p_i * ln(p_i)). Session 043 baseline H ~= 0.3 (25/29 skew). Target H >= 1.5. FALSIFICATION: max-concept has >60% of total memberships. METRIC 2 (Steering Actionability): For each frontier recommendation shown during observations, the agent scores: 2=immediately actionable, 1=reasonable but vague, 0=unhelpful/wrong. Target mean >= 1.5. FALSIFICATION: mean < 1.0. METRIC 3 (Prediction Error): After harvest, compare predicted delta-F(S) for top-3 recommendations vs actual. Compute mean(|predicted - actual|). Session 038 baseline 0.224. Target <= 0.20. FALSIFICATION: > 0.30. Composite score: entropy(30%) + actionability(40%) + prediction_error(30%), normalized to 10-point scale. Pass: >= 8/10. Traces to: INV-GUIDANCE-014, ADR-FOUNDATION-030.; DOGFOOD subagent prompt design: The subagent must be a clean-context agent that interacts with braid as a real user would (Session 034 pattern). The prompt prescribes a structured lifecycle but does NOT give the agent any braid internals knowledge. The agent should: (1) cd to Go CLI dir, (2) run braid init, (3) run braid status to verify, (4) make 10 observations about the Go CLI codebase — 3 about well-explored packages (parser, storage, events), 3 about unexplored packages (witness, challenge, absorb), 2 cross-cutting (error handling, testing), 2 architectural (coupling, module boundaries) — each with genuine domain insight and appropriate confidence levels, (5) after each observation, record the frontier recommendation text and score its actionability 0-2, (6) run braid harvest --commit, (7) run braid status --verbose and capture concept distribution, (8) compute entropy H = -sum(p_i * ln(p_i)), (9) report all measurements. The agent must NOT be told about innate concepts, CCE internals, or expected outcomes — it is a blind evaluator. Traces to: INV-GUIDANCE-014, C7, C8.; Session entity: :task/t-c9d6a75c; DOGFOOD store reset justification: The S045-UPGRADE task (t-a49bce38) proposed adding a braid upgrade command, but on reflection, clearing and re-initializing is superior for this specific case: (1) The Go CLI store has 290 txns of cruft from 5 prior dogfood sessions with different braid versions, different schema states, and contradictory concept assignments. Upgrading would preserve this pollution. (2) A fresh init IS the user experience — new users won't have legacy stores. Testing upgrade is testing an edge case; testing init tests the common path. (3) The 290-txn store data has already been analyzed and scored (3.3, 5.3, 6.7, 3.5). The data is captured in braid observations in the MAIN store. Nothing is lost by clearing the DOGFOOD store. (4) C1 (append-only) applies within a store's lifetime, not across store lifetimes. Re-init is not a C1 violation — it's creating a new store. Close t-a49bce38 as 'deferred — clear+reinit is the right approach for dogfood; upgrade command is a separate future feature.' Traces to: INV-STORE-001, C7.; DOGFOOD-2 Session 3 RETRY — 7 bugs found by subagent: (1) CRITICAL: Concept collapse — all concepts jaccard=1.00, zero discriminative power. Hash embedder cosine always above JOIN_THRESHOLD=0.20. (2) HIGH: Frontier recommendation degeneration — only 2-3 templates, never conditions on observation text or exploration history. Mean actionability 0.2/2.0. (3) MEDIUM: Harvest drift=1.00 after 10 rich observations — should be decreasing. (4) MEDIUM: TSV format prepends routing metadata before query results. (5) LOW: Category assignment inconsistency (spec-insight vs observation). (6) LOW: Bridge recommendation uses raw entity hash instead of title (note: entity_label L1-REV partially fixed this but hash still appears for some entities without :db/ident). (7) LOW: concept/member-count query returns all historical values in append-only store. Subagent also identified 7 missing features: file-aware observations, observation search/recall, concept rename/split/merge commands, guided exploration mode, observation diffing, code structure integration, batch observe.; Session entity: :task/t-9b539223" :op :assert}
